{
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Choose an area of nonmagical flame that you can see and that fits within a 5-foot &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} within range. You can extinguish the &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} in that area, and you create either fireworks or smoke when you do so.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>Fireworks</strong><em><strong>.</strong></em> </span>The target explodes with a dazzling display of colors. Each creature within 10 feet of the target must succeed on a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw or become &amp;Reference[blinded]{blinded} until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>Smoke.</strong> </span>Thick black smoke spreads out from the target in a 20-foot radius, moving around corners. The area of the smoke is heavily obscured. The smoke persists for 1 minute or until a strong wind disperses it.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
